
/*
 * Lists all files within a specified folder and its subfolders recursively. The [io.file.list-recursively] slot is used to retrieve files from a directory structure, while the [strings.concat] slot is used to concatenate the results into a single string. This allows for a comprehensive overview of all files within a directory and its nested directories.
 * 
 * 1. [io.file.list-recursively] - Lists all files within a specified folder and its subfolders recursively.
 * 2. [strings.concat] - Concatenates the results of the file listing into a single string.
 */
io.file.list-recursively:x:@strings.concat
